      \captionof{figure}{Illustrating the relationship between the angle between vectors and the sign of their dot product.} We <em>can</em> use <xref ref="thm_dot_product">Theorem</xref> to compute the dot product, but generally this theorem is used to find the angle between known vectors (since the dot product is generally easy to compute). To this end, we rewrite the theorem's equation as
      <me>
        \cos(\theta) = \frac{\dotp uv}{\norm{\vec u}\norm{\vec v}}  \Leftrightarrow  \theta = \cos^{-1}\left(\frac{\dotp uv}{\norm{\vec u}\norm{\vec v}}\right).
      </me>
    </p>

